descriptionMarkdown:
Input the desired number of science packs in orbit as the 'checkmark' signal, and the contents of the orbital logsitics network into the signal receiver, and this will calculate how much material is missing and pack that many basic science packs and the raw materials for that many space science packs into the rocket.

The constant combiners in the lower left are doing some math to get around the integer only restriction; the one with rocket fuel, processing units etc. shows how many of each thing you need per X space science packs, and the combiner with science packs sets X. You could change these to request materials for just about anything, but you have to do this math yourself. Personally, I used Factory Planner.

Overfills a bit due to outstanding logistics requests. Doesn't launch automatically.
title: [Space Exploration] Science requester [wip}
